# How-To Update Bindings When gtfs-realtime.proto Changes

When
[gtfs-realtime.proto](https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs-realtime/gtfs-realtime-proto)
is updated, the various languages bindings must be regenerated, packaged, and
deployed.  These instructions will walk you through the process.

## Java, Python, Ruby

The following command can be used to regenrate the source-code for Java,
Python, and Ruby, all using the Google protoc compiler.

```
protoc \
--java_out=java/src/main/java \
--python_out=python/google/transit \
--ruby_out=ruby/lib/google/transit \
gtfs-realtime.proto
```

## Node.js

From the `nodejs` directory, run the following command:

```
npm run buildProto
```